# Capture Filters

Capture filters reduce captured traffic.

Examples:

Capture only HTTP:

```
port 80
```

Capture HTTPS:

```
port 443
```

Capture DNS:

```
port 53
```

Capture one host:

```
host 192.168.1.10
```

Capture TCP:

```
tcp
```

Capture UDP:

```
udp
```

---

# Display Filters

Display filters hide unwanted packets after capture.

## IP Address

```
ip.addr == 192.168.1.5
```

Source IP

```
ip.src == 192.168.1.5
```

Destination IP

```
ip.dst == 192.168.1.5
```

---

## TCP

```
tcp
```

TCP Port

```
tcp.port == 80
```

Source Port

```
tcp.srcport == 443
```

Destination Port

```
tcp.dstport == 80
```

---

## UDP

```
udp
```

UDP Port

```
udp.port == 53
```

---

## HTTP

```
http
```

HTTP GET

```
http.request.method == "GET"
```

HTTP POST

```
http.request.method == "POST"
```

---

## DNS

```
dns
```

DNS Query

```
dns.flags.response == 0
```

DNS Response

```
dns.flags.response == 1
```

---

## ICMP

```
icmp
```

---

## ARP

```
arp
```

---

## HTTPS (TLS)

```
tls
```

Older versions:

```
ssl
```

