# Practical Workflow

1. Open PCAP file.
2. Apply display filters.
3. Identify protocols.
4. Follow streams.
5. Check statistics.
6. Export objects if needed.
7. Document findings.

---

# Wireshark Tips

- Capture only necessary traffic.
- Use display filters extensively.
- Learn common protocol ports.
- Save important captures.
- Colorize suspicious traffic.
- Inspect packet details layer by layer.
- Use Follow Stream for application data.
- Use Statistics to identify anomalies.

