# Exam Tips

- Capture filters are applied **before** capturing.
- Display filters are applied **after** capturing.
- Wireshark does **not** modify packets; it only captures and analyzes them.
- Packet analysis follows the encapsulation model (Ethernet → IP → TCP/UDP → Application).
- Follow Stream reconstructs complete conversations.
- Protocol Hierarchy provides an overview of protocols in the capture.
- Export Objects can recover transferred files.
- Display filters are one of the most important features to master.

